[{"id":"VH917217","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a horizontal segment of wire in a uniform magnetic field and a force diagram. The wire segment has a length of 50 centimeters. The magnetic field has a magnitude of 0.50 Tesla and is represented by evenly spaced crosses. The force diagram shows a force F sub B toward the top of the page and a force m g toward the bottom of the page.\" height=\"193\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH917217.g02.png\" width=\"270\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The horizontal segment of wire of length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"50 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"50 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>50</mn><mo>⁢</mo><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mtext>  </mtext><mi>c</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.010 kilogram\"><math alttext=\"0.010 kilogram\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mn>0.010</mn><mtext> </mtext><mtext> </mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> shown is connected to a circuit (not shown) and carries a current of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.50 ampere\"><math alttext=\"0.50 ampere\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.50</mn><mo>⁢</mo><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mtext>  </mtext><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to the right. The wire is released from rest in a uniform magnetic field of magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.50 Tesla\"><math alttext=\"0.50 Tesla\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.50</mn><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mrow><mtext>  </mtext><mi>T</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The force diagram for the wire shows the directions of the forces but not their magnitudes. What is the magnitude of the acceleration of the wire?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH917217_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.025 meters per second squared\"><math alttext=\"0.025 meters per second squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.025</mn><mo>⁢</mo><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mtext>  </mtext><mi>m</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.5 meters per second squared\"><math alttext=\"2.5 meters per second squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2.5</mn><mtext> </mtext><mtext> </mtext><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mi>m</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"22.5 meters per second squared\"><math alttext=\"22.5 meters per second squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>22.5</mn><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mtext>  </mtext><mi>m</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1240 meters per second squared\"><math alttext=\"1240 meters per second squared\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1240</mn><mtext> </mtext><mstyle mathvariant=\"normal\"><mi>m</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mstyle><mtext> </mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]